1242":"1242","<of, Gerardstown, Meath, Ireland>":"Ireland","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Bermingham","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Irish Liam, Sinead.","Irish (of English origin): variant of   Birmingham  . This form of the surname is found mainly in Ireland.","History: The Bermingham family take their surname from lands held at what is now a great city in the West Midlands of England, but it was brought to Ireland as early as the 12th century. The Norman baron Robert de Bermyngeham was a follower of Strongbow (see   Clare  ); his name is found on a number of Irish charters between 1175 and 1179. The family was also known as <i>Mac Fheorais</i> (see   Corish  ) in Ireland, named for Piers (Gaelic <i>Feoras</i>) de Bermyngeham, the father of Robert."],"variants":[{"name":"Birmingham","meanings":["English: habitational name from Birmingham in the West Midlands. In Domesday Book the name is already found as <i>Bermingeham</i>, but it seems likely that it was originally <i>Beornmundingahām</i> ‘homestead (Old English <i>hām</i>) of the people of (<i>-inga-</i>) <i>Beornmund</i>’, a personal name composed of the elements <i>beorn</i> ‘young man, warrior’ + <i>mund</i> ‘protection’. This surname is established in Ireland (see   Bermingham  )."]},{"name":"Corish","meanings":["Irish:","shortened form of <i>Mac Fheorais</i> ‘son of Piers’. The name was borne by a Connacht family descended from Piers de Bermingham, second lord of Athenry in Galway (died <i>c.</i> 1309). Compare   Bermingham  .","shortened form of <i>Mac Muirghis</i> ‘son of <i>Maurice</i>’, a personal name introduced to Ireland by the Normans. Compare   Morrissey  ."]}]},{"name":"De","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["‘Attainment’."],"variants":[]},{"name":"Atheny","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["In classical mythology the name of the Greek goddess of wisdom and patron of Athens."],"variants":[{"name":"Athina","meanings":["In classical mythology the name of the Greek goddess of wisdom and patron of Athens."]},{"name":"Athena","meanings":["In classical mythology the name of the Greek goddess of wisdom and patron of Athens."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Lord De Atheny Bermingham was born about 1234, in Ireland. He had at least 1 daughter."},"et":{"ABT 1234–":"umbes 1234–Surnud","1242–Female":"1242–Surnud","1234–Male":"1234–Surnud","1234":"1234","ABT 1234":"umbes 1234","1242":"1242","<of, Gerardstown, Meath, Ireland>":"Iirimaa"},"fi":{"ABT 1234–":"noin 1234–Kuollut","1242–Female":"1242–Kuollut","1234–Male":"1234–Kuollut","1234":"1234","ABT 1234":"noin 1234","1242":"1242","<of, Gerardstown, Meath, Ireland>":"Irlanti"},"fr":{"ABT 1234–":"environ 1234–Décédé","1242–Female":"1242–Décédée","1234–Male":"1234–Décédé","1234":"1234","ABT 1234":"environ 1234","1242":"1242","<of, Gerardstown, Meath, Ireland>":"Irlande","lifeSummary":"Lord De Atheny Bermingham est né environ 1234, à Irlande. Il a eu au moins 1 fille."},"de":{"ABT 1234–":"um 1234–Verstorben","1242–Female":"1242–Verstorben","1234–Male":"1234–Verstorben","1234":"1234","ABT 1234":"um 1234","1242":"1242","<of, Gerardstown, Meath, Ireland>":"Irland","lifeSummary":"Lord De Atheny Bermingham wurde um 1234 in Irland geboren. Er hatte mindestens 1 Tochter."},"ht":{"ABT 1234–":"about 1234–Desede","1242–Female":"1242–Desede","1234–Male":"1234–Desede","1234":"1234","ABT 1234":"about 1234","1242":"1242","<of, Gerardstown, Meath, Ireland>":"Irlande"},"hu":{"ABT 1234–":"1234 körül–elhunyt","1242–Female":"1242–elhunyt","1234–Male":"1234–elhunyt","1234":"1234","ABT 1234":"1234 körül","1242":"1242","<of, Gerardstown, Meath, Ireland>":"Írország"},"id":{"ABT 1234–":"sekitar 1234–Telah Meninggal","1242–Female":"1242–Telah Meninggal","1234–Male":"1234–Telah Meninggal","1234